cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper deals with the problem of landmark detection using deep learning and model-based methods. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for classification of landmarks from RGB images and LiDAR point clouds suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of model-based methods and prior knowledge of previous time steps suggests that the paper also belongs to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of deep learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of natural language processing techniques for semantic landmark detection suggests that the paper may also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
